.TH "request_partial_firmware_into_buf" 9 "request_partial_firmware_into_buf" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
request_partial_firmware_into_buf \- load partial firmware into a previously allocated buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" request_partial_firmware_into_buf
.BI "(const struct firmware **firmware_p "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "struct device *device "  ","
.BI "void *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "size_t offset "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "firmware_p" 12
pointer to firmware image
.IP "name" 12
name of firmware file
.IP "device" 12
device for which firmware is being loaded and DMA region allocated
.IP "buf" 12
address of buffer to load firmware into
.IP "size" 12
size of buffer
.IP "offset" 12
offset into file to read
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function works pretty much like request_firmware_into_buf except
it allows a partial read of the file.
